    <text>
        <body>
            <div type="edition" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="grc" resp="#JP #NQ">
                <ab>
                    <lb n="1" xml:id="BSοAK"/><space quantity="4" unit="character" xml:id="BSοAU"/><w xml:id="BSοAe">ὁ</w> <w xml:id="BSοAo">δᾶμος</w> <space quantity="3" unit="character" xml:id="BSοAy"/>
                    <lb n="2" xml:id="BSοAΙ"/><w xml:id="BSοAΤ"><unclear xml:id="BSοAε">Β</unclear>ίωτον</w> <w xml:id="BSοAο">Τιμάνδρο<supplied reason="lost" xml:id="BSοBA">υ</supplied></w> 
                    <lb n="3" xml:id="BSοBK"/><w xml:id="BSοBU">εὐνοίας</w> <w xml:id="BSοBe">ἕνεκε<unclear xml:id="BSοBo">ν</unclear></w>
                </ab>
            </div>
            <div type="apparatus">
                <listApp>
                    <app><note>Text based upon autopsy</note></app>
                    <app loc="2"><note>Salinas: [Κ]ίωτον; Kaibel: [Β]ίωτον; lapis: trace of upper eye of Β (contra Salinas, trace of K).</note></app>
                </listApp>
            </div>
            <div type="translation" xml:lang="it" resp="#NQ">
                <p>Il damos (onora) Biotos figlio di Timandros per benevolenza</p>
            </div>
            <div type="translation" xml:lang="en" resp="#JP">
                <p>The people (honours) Biotos son of Timandros, for the sake of goodwill</p>
            </div>
            <div type="commentary">
                <p>Notwithstanding the damage, it is clear that there was no ethnic included in the first part of the text, and the inscription appears complete. The name <foreign xml:lang="grc">Βίωτος</foreign> is also attested on tile and amphora stamps from southern Italy; no other form ending -ιωτος is known from the region.</p>
            </div>
